PN,43902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1779274977
OL,3,CDog rescued by RNLI after falling onto
OL,4,Crocks from coastal path
OL,6,FThe crew member was able to climb the
OL,7,Frocks and grab the dog. He then swam
OL,8,Fback to the boat - carrying the dog -
OL,9,Fand both were hauled aboard.
OL,11,FAfter a short journey back to the
OL,12,Flifeboat station, the dog was reunited
OL,13,Fwith its owners, who had been watching
OL,14,Fnervously from the path above.
OL,16,FThe relieved owners later sent a
OL,17,Fmessage to the RNLI: "We can't thank
OL,18,Fyou enough for saving our beloved dog.
OL,19,FShe's fine - subdued and exhausted but
OL,20,Fnot so much that she couldn't manage
OL,21,Fsome toast in a restaurant".
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/3
